0e72dcb5-c7db-42a9-be1f-5b0362de7db8.description=
Loops over a specified amount of time and averages a value fed into it over this time. Checks to see if this value is above or below a specified threshold.
This flow should only be used as a subflow since using it on its own will always return the continue response unless runLength is assigned a value of 0.
When this flow gives the continue response the calling flow must obtain another value, and pass it to this flow again.

Inputs\:
runLength - The number of seconds this flow should loop.
waitTime - The number of seconds this flow should wait before returning when looping.
threshold - A value to compare the averaged value to.
value - The value of the most recent function call, which will be added to the average.
list - The list of values that will be used for finding the average.
timeStarted - Time at which the flow is started.

Responses\:
less than - The average was less than the threshold.
equal - The average was the same as the threshold.
greater than - The average was greater than the threshold.
Continue - The specified amount of time has not yet passed, the calling flow should run another operation and pass this flow another value.
failure - values in keyName could not be averaged.

Extra results\:
average - The average value of the list. only a result if the response is success.
list - A list that is accumulating values. This is erased when the time runs out.
timeStarted - The time since you made the first function call. this is erased when time runs out.
